1 (h) To carry out the functions relating to its duties and responsibilities, the board
2 is empowered to receive donations and grants of funds; to appoint consultants
3 as needed; and to sponsor studies, conduct conferences, and publish
4 information.
5 Section 2. KRS 161.030 is amended to read as follows:
6 (1) Notwithstanding the age of the pupil, the certification of all teachers and other
7 school personnel, in public schools only, is vested in the Education Professional
8 Standards Board. When so certified, teachers and other school personnel shall not
9 be required to have licensure, certification, or other forms of approval from any
10 other state agency for the performance of their respective assignments within the
11 system of public schools, except as provided for by law. All certificates authorized
12 under KRS 161.010 to 161.126 shall be issued in accordance with the
13 administrative regulations of the Education Professional Standards Board. After
14 July 15, 1994, all certificate applications and other data collection instruments of
15 the board shall include a request for voluntary information about the applicant's
16 ethnic background. This information shall be available to help local school districts
17 locate minority candidates. A person who holds a certificate prior to this
18 requirement may request that ethnic information be added to his or her file. Nothing
19 in this section shall preclude the right of an individual in a nonpublic school from
20 seeking voluntary certification by the Education Professional Standards Board.
21 (2) Certificates shall be issued upon written application and in accordance with statutes
22 and regulations in effect at the time of application to persons who have completed,
23 at colleges, universities, or local school district programs approved by the
24 Education Professional Standards Board for the preparation of teachers and other
25 school personnel, the curricula prescribed by the administrative regulations of the
26 Education Professional Standards Board.
27 (3) (a) 1. Certification of all new teachers and teachers seeking additional
Page 8 of 12
BR130900.100 - 1309 - XXXX 1/29/2026 2:18 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1309
1 certification shall require the successful completion of appropriate
2 assessments prior to certification. The assessments shall be selected by
3 the Education Professional Standards Board and shall measure
4 knowledge in the specific teaching field of the applicant, including
5 content of the field and teaching of that content. The Education
6 Professional Standards Board shall determine the minimum acceptable
7 level of achievement on each assessment. The assessments shall
8 measure those concepts, ideas, and facts which are being taught in
9 teacher education programs in Kentucky. Upon successful completion of
10 the assessments and the approved teacher preparation program, a
11 professional certificate valid for five (5) years shall be issued.
12 2. Beginning July 1, 2027, the academic content assessments required
13 for applicants in each certification selected by the Education
14 Professional Standards Board shall be limited to the academic content
15 area or areas in which an applicant is seeking certification. The
16 academic content assessments selected shall be narrowly tailored to
17 ensure academic achievement and competency of an applicant in the
18 academic content area the applicant is seeking certification.
19 (b) If an applicant for teacher certification has completed the approved teacher
20 preparation program and has taken but failed to successfully complete the
21 appropriate assessments selected by the Education Professional Standards
22 Board, a conditional certificate may be issued for a period not to exceed one
23 (1) year. The employing school district, in collaboration with the teacher
24 education institution, shall provide technical assistance and mentoring support
25 to the conditionally certified teacher. The teacher shall retake the assessments
26 during the validity period of the conditional certificate. The conditional
27 certificate shall not be reissued. Upon successful completion of the required
Page 9 of 12
BR130900.100 - 1309 - XXXX 1/29/2026 2:18 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1309
1 assessments, a professional certificate valid for five (5) years shall be issued.
2 The Education Professional Standards Board shall promulgate administrative
3 regulations to establish the standards and procedures for issuance of a
4 conditional certificate.
5 (c) If an out-of-state teacher with less than two (2) years' experience comes to
6 Kentucky after the deadline for taking the assessments, a temporary certificate
7 may be issued for a period up to six (6) months. The teacher shall take the
8 assessments during the period of the temporary certificate. If the teacher fails
9 the assessments, the temporary certificate shall be valid only for the current
10 semester. If the teacher passes the assessments, a professional certificate valid
11 for five (5) years shall be issued.
12 (4) A reasonable fee to be paid by the teacher and directly related to the actual cost of
13 the administration of the assessments shall be established by the Education
14 Professional Standards Board. Provisions shall be made for persons having less than
15 minimum levels of performance on any assessment to repeat that assessment, and
16 candidates shall be informed of their strengths and weaknesses in the specific
17 performance areas. The Education Professional Standards Board shall provide for
18 confidentiality of the individual assessment scores. Scores shall be available only to
19 the candidate and to the education officials who are responsible for determining
20 whether established certification standards have been met. Scores shall be used only
21 in the assessment for certification of new teachers and of out-of-state teachers with
22 less than two (2) years of teaching experience who are seeking initial certification
23 in Kentucky.
24 (5) If an applicant establishes eligibility for a five (5) year professional certificate under
25 the provisions of subsection (3)(a) of this section, the applicant shall also be eligible
26 for the issuance of a certificate for substitute teaching as provided by the
27 administrative regulations of the Education Professional Standards Board.
