1 (6) (a) The Education Professional Standards Board shall issue a ten (10) year
2 emeritus certificate to an applicant who has:
3 1. Retired or will retire not more than one (1) year prior to the expiration
4 date of the certificate;
5 2. Met the requirements to receive an emeritus certificate as set forth in
6 administrative regulation promulgated by the Education Professional
7 Standards Board; and
8 3. Completed the required application unless the provisions of KRS
9 161.120 apply.
10 (b) The Education Professional Standards Board shall issue a one (1) time five (5)
11 year exception certificate to an individual:
12 1. Whose certificate has expired;
13 2. Whose rank upon expiration was Rank I or Rank II;
14 3. Who has met the requirements to receive an exception certificate as set
15 forth in administrative regulation promulgated by the Education
16 Professional Standards Board;
17 4. Who completed three (3) years of classroom instruction prior to the
18 certificate's expiration; and
19 5. Who has completed the required application unless the provisions of
20 KRS 161.120 apply.
21 (7) The Education Professional Standards Board shall approve the curricula of any
22 college or university, or of any department thereof, for the training of teachers, and
23 any nontraditional or alternative teacher preparation program offered in a public or
24 private postsecondary education institution, private contractor, or state agency, and
25 shall also approve the curricula of any local district alternative certification
26 program, when the curricula comply with the administrative regulations of the
27 Education Professional Standards Board for the issuance of certificates and when
Page 11 of 12
BR130900.100 - 1309 - XXXX 1/29/2026 2:18 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1309
1 the institution has met the terms and conditions provided in KRS 161.010 to
2 161.120. Any student who has completed any of these curricula, as approved by the
3 Education Professional Standards Board, and who has completed the prescribed
4 requirements for the issuance of certificates shall be granted a certificate
5 corresponding to the curricula completed.
6 (8) The issuance of any certificate, except emergency certificates issued pursuant to
7 KRS 161.100, by the Education Professional Standards Board shall not be
8 dependent upon an offer of employment. The certification process, except for
9 emergency certificates, is independent of any job prospects and certification shall
10 be awarded on the basis of completing a teacher preparation program or an
11 alternative certification pathway and passing required assessments.
